From: Apollo Linux Team <dev@apollolinux.org>
Subject: [PATCH 09/12] nvidia-390xx: fix drm_gem_prime (kernel 6.10)

Kernel 6.10 reorganized the DRM GEM prime helpers.
drm_gem_prime_export/import are no longer in nvidia's used path.
drm_prime_sg_to_page_addr_arrays removed.

Also handles removal of __vmalloc fallback path used in UVM.

Signed-off-by: Apollo Linux Team <dev@apollolinux.org>
---
diff --git a/kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-prime-fence.c b/kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-prime-fence.c
--- a/kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-prime-fence.c
+++ b/kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-prime-fence.c
@@ -1,8 +1,16 @@
+#include <linux/version.h>
+
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(6, 10, 0)
+/* drm_prime_sg_to_page_addr_arrays removed — use scatterlist iteration */
+#define NV_PRIME_SG_TO_PAGES(sg, pages, addrs, nents) \
+    do { \
+        struct scatterlist *__sg; unsigned int __i = 0; \
+        for_each_sg((sg), __sg, (nents), __i) { \
+            (pages)[__i] = sg_page(__sg); \
+            if (addrs) (addrs)[__i] = sg_phys(__sg); \
+        } \
+    } while (0)
+#else
+#define NV_PRIME_SG_TO_PAGES(sg, pages, addrs, nents) \
+    drm_prime_sg_to_page_addr_arrays(sg, pages, addrs, nents)
+#endif
